post_text: SMS Text messaging coming soon via School Messenger (current company who our phone messages are managed by). We feel that it will be yet another way that we can work to communicate with everyone effectively. As we get closer to the "opt-in" date there will be more reminders. Essentially, there will be a special 6 digit number that you'll have to text (or will receive a text from) to "opt-in." Upon opting in you will then be able to receive the text updates that the school sends too. If you "opt-out," that's ok too, but just know that you won't receive those texts from us. Please spread the word and we'll have more information as we get closer to our opt-in date. Thanks everyone!

Good afternoon,

We hope this message finds you and your families safe and enjoying the summer weather. Due to the current circumstances surrounding COVID 19 and continued social distancing recommendations, Mr. Fischer and myself have decided to cancel the ORR Prom that had been re-scheduled for Thursday, June 25th. This was truly a difficult decision and we do hope to hold a Fall Dance where both schools will be able to participate in once the school year gets going!

Thanks, Mr. Books

May 17, 2020 - A day that Rutland's seniors had been looking forward to for a long time...Graduation! Unfortunately, due to COVID-19, the ceremony and celebration had to be postponed.

Please take a few minutes to recognize/learn/know more about our 12 amazing graduates!

Then...please save the date!!! July 25th, 2020 is the new date for the seniors to be recognized with a graduation ceremony. It would be amazing to pack the town of Rutland to say hello and cheer for each of these individual's accomplishments! We honestly hope you can make it!!!!

Congratulations to the 2020 graduating class of Rutland High School! I can't wait to personally tell each of you directly.

post_text:
Results from last night's Virtual FFA State Convention. Bri Primm received 6th place Gold and Emily Nold placed 28th Bronze to lead Rutland's 9th place Bronze Horse Selection Team! Other team members were Ryan Sievers and Rylie Aschmeller. Emily Nold also placed 11th Gold to lead Rutland's Livestock Team including Colton Wicks and Kayla Price. Brandon Trygstad's 17th Bronze placing in Milk Quality and Products lead the team including Jacob Jaton and Koby Pust.
Rutland's Ag Mechanics team placed 11th for a Bronze Award. Team members were JJ Agnew, Issac Trygstad, Daniel Jaton and Caleb Jaton. Shayne Devaney, Charlie Jeratowski and Mya Hamer represented Rutland FFA as the Agronomy Team which placed 11th of 19 teams. Congratulations to you all, proud you could show them how it is done from your living room! Mr.E.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

The District will be providing free Grab and Go lunches (for students) to those who responded yes via the survey monkey that was sent out yesterday. Starting Monday, lunches will be available each weekday from 11:30 am to 12:00 pm by the south entrance of the lunch room. The meals will be designed to be picked up and taken home to eat. Please send individuals who are feeling healthy...we ask those not feeling well to stay home. No paperwork or signatures are required, we just ask that the lunches go to students of the district only please. Thank you for all of your flexibility and understanding through this time! We appreciate it more than you know!

***IF you were not able to respond to the survey and would like to participate in this program, please email Brian.brosnahan@k12.sd.us and let him know how many student lunches you'd like, and he'll be sure to inform Beth and Kim of the additional need. Thanks again!

Brian

post_text:
Good Evening Raiders! As of today, we will be closed through March 27th, as Governor Noem recommended a one week extension to the school closure earlier today. Over the next couple of days your child(ren)'s teacher(s) will be reaching out to provide further instructions regarding coursework for next week, as well as outline their availability during the day. If you have questions, please reach out to them and be sure to use your time for meaningful learning.

Between now and next week I encourage you to utilize many of the vast online resources that have been shared (here on our FB page...with most, if not all, being FREE), have your kids reading independently (yes, for fun!), or feel free to check out this link as well (https://sdsfec.org/homelearning) from the SD Statewide Family Engagement Center. The "newness" of everything may seem overwhelming, but I can assure you, our staff has (and is) working hard to make sure that they're available to every student and are focused on providing meaningful work/assignments/projects for your child(ren). Thank you!

post_text: Congratulations to the Rutland FFA members attending the District 2 Leadership CDE Monday night. The Sales Team consisting of Brandon and Isaac Trygstad and Daniel and Caleb Jaton placed 1st! The Marketing Plan team consisting of Bri Primm, JJ Agnew, Jacob Jaton and Josie Timm placed 2nd! Josie Timm also placed 3rd in Ag Broadcasting! Bri Primm was also selected as the District Treasure. Daniel Jaton placed 4th in Extemporaneous Speaking. All of these students will attend the State FFA Leadership CDE December 8th and 9th in Pierre. Other members participating on Monday night were Mya Hamer in Extemp , Ryan Sievers in Creed, Colton Wicks in Employment Skills, and Koby Pust in Ag Broadcasting.

post_text: Good morning! On November 11th the Rutland School would like to invite veterans and community members to our annual Veteran's Day program. Registration for veterans will begin around 8:30 with breakfast provided by the Class of 2020 for our veterans and honored guests. The Order of Events/Program will begin around 9:00. Mailed letters and invites will be sent in the next few days. We have our ongoing mailing list of invitees but PLEASE RSVP Janet at the school if you are a Veteran and would like to attend and be recognized in your branch of service and rank. Our Staff, students and public would like to honor you on this special day! Thank you and we hope to see you there!

post_text: My favorite Personal Finance lesson is called Family Reality Check! Groups randomly choose their family make-up, unexpected expenses, family annual income, and credit card payments. They then have to put together a working budget using all expenses. How amazed they are with the cost of everything! Most groups are having to decide what they can do without in order to balance their budgets! Real life!
